    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "97884618_266b62dd",
        "filename": "minijail0_cli.c",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 1628636
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-09T12:55:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually, if I use int here, I make it impossible to specify any gid \u003e 2^32/2. gid_t size and signedness is system dependent, and I thought it was a good idea to avoid making any assumption about it (and using int does make an assumption, that happens to be wrong on my x86_64 system).\nIf I keep gid_t:\n\n# minijail0 -u 1 -g 2 --add-supp-group $((2**32-2)) /usr/bin/id\nuid\u003d1(daemon) gid\u003d2(bin) groups\u003d2(bin),4294967294\n\nIf I replace it by int:\n# minijail0 -u 1 -g 2 --add-supp-group $((2**32-2)) /usr/bin/id\nuid\u003d1(daemon) gid\u003d2(bin) groups\u003d2(bin),2147483648\n\nNote that actually, this is also true for -u and -g for now as they use int:\n\n# minijail0 -u $((2**32-2)) -g $((2**32-2)) --add-supp-group $((2**32-2)) /usr/bin/id\nuid\u003d2147483648 gid\u003d2147483648 groups\u003d2147483648\n\nSo I\u0027ll use int for this patchset for consistency, but if you agree with me that this is a bug, I can submit a separate patchset to fix -u, -g and --add-supp-group together (because if we do this, I think we want this to be visible in git log).\n\nBTW a fixed version looks like this:\n# minijail0 -u $((2**32-2)) -g $((2**32-2)) --add-supp-group $((2**32-3)) /usr/bin/id\nuid\u003d4294967294 gid\u003d4294967294 groups\u003d4294967294,4294967293",
      "parentUuid": "d5be1576_145e35a9",
      "revId": "a77d95dce36f856c11ff06e14c54db4fbe3d34d6",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
